Who are we?

</h2>

<!-- ================================= -->

<div class="info-card">

<div class="about-title">

<img
src="/images/logo-small.png"
alt="Logo"
class="about-logo">

<h3>

About the Association

</h3>

</div>

<p>

Based on the lofty royal vision of the importance and antiquity of the city of Tangier and the strengthening of its role as a global beacon of civilizational, cultural and artistic influence, and in keeping with the great cultural and civilizational achievements witnessed by the city of Tangier and the cities of northern Morocco and the Kingdom of Morocco, the Afaq Tangier Association was founded through the efforts of a group of Moroccan and Arab artists and intellectuals after it was a cultural and artistic dream that the group worked on, as their experiences and dreams combined with the aim of sharing these cultural experiences and artistic techniques and presenting everything that is cultural, artistic and creative contemporary to Moroccan youth, and creating cultural and artistic partnerships that work on the ancient Moroccan heritage values, and extend bridges of civilizational, cultural and artistic communication between Morocco and the world.
</p>

<div class="about-images">

<img src="/images/about1.jpg" alt="">
<img src="/images/about2.jpg" alt="">
<img src="/images/about3.jpg" alt="">

</div>

</div>

<!-- ================================= -->

<div class="info-card">

<h3>

Our strategy for this year and the next five years
2024 - 2030

</h3>

<p>

    <p>
       Our vision:
    </p>



Our vision, starting from 2024 and the coming years, is based on developing our studios and workshops, promoting professional cultural and artistic productions, organizing meetings, festivals and forums, and opening up to new cities and villages within the Kingdom, while building fruitful national and international partnerships that contribute to delivering our message to every child, boy, young man and woman throughout Morocco.

<p>

Our message:

</p>

Our children are the wealth of the future... ambassadors of Moroccan national identity, culture and art.

<p>

Our strategic goals:

</p>

Reaching the largest possible number of the Kingdom’s children, and enabling them to employ their creative abilities to produce content that carries the authentic Moroccan identity, with attention to girls, people with special needs, and students who have dropped out of school, and reintegrating them into society through culture and arts.

<p>

   Target groups:

</p>

Gifted children, boys, girls, young people, people with special needs, and anyone who has the desire to participate in cultural and artistic activities, regardless of their age.

</p>

<div class="festival-images">


<img src="/images/OurStrategy/photo2.jpg" alt="">


</div>

