<h3>

Day Two

</h3>

<h4>

Saturday, April 19, 2025

</h4>

<p>

Hassanouna Youth Center hosted film screenings and professional workshops including:

</p>

<ul>

<li>

How to Produce Your First Film.

</li>

<li>

Festival Guests Film Screenings.

</li>

<li>

Participants' Film Discussions.

</li>

<li>

Open Meetings with Film Directors.

</li>

</ul>

<p>

The workshops featured directors from:

</p>

<ul>

<li>

Morocco.

</li>

<li>

United Arab Emirates.

</li>

<li>

Sultanate of Oman.

</li>

</ul>

<p>

Approximately 120 young participants, journalists, filmmakers, and cinema enthusiasts attended the event.

</p>

<div class="festival-images">

<img src="/images/day2/photo1.jpg" alt="">
<img src="/images/day2/photo2.jpg" alt="">
<img src="/images/day2/photo3.jpg" alt="">

</div>

</div>

<!-- ============================================= -->

<div class="festival-card">

<h3>

Day Three

</h3>

<h4>

Sunday, April 20, 2025

</h4>

<p>

The final day featured the International Conference entitled:

</p>

<h4>

Identity in Traditional and Digital Audiovisual Production

</h4>

<p>

The conference brought together a number of filmmakers and media experts from Morocco, Iraq, the United Arab Emirates, and the Sultanate of Oman. It also welcomed a social media influencer with disabilities, who shared her inspiring personal experience.

</p>

<p>

The winners of both the Classical and Digital Competitions were announced, followed by artistic and musical performances. The festival concluded with a guided tour through the historic Medina of Tangier, allowing international guests to discover the city's rich historical and cultural identity.

</p>

